# ==============================================================================
# Trivy Vulnerability Ignore List
# ==============================================================================
#
# This file contains CVEs that are intentionally ignored during security scans.
# Each entry should have a comment explaining why it's ignored.
#
# Syntax: CVE-ID [exp:yyyy-mm-dd] — Trivy stops ignoring after expiry date
# Documentation: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
#
# AUTOMATED REVIEW: .github/workflows/security-review.yml checks quarterly
# if ignored CVEs have become fixable and creates issues for review.

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ncurses: Buffer overflow (CVE-2025-69720) - HIGH
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Status: No fix available in Debian Bookworm (as of 2026-06-13)
# Packages: libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base, ncurses-bin
# Impact: Minimal - ncurses is not directly exposed to user input in our container
# Mitigation: Container runs as non-root, no interactive shell exposed
# Auto-expires: 2026-09-13 (forces re-evaluation after 3 months)
CVE-2025-69720 exp:2026-09-13

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# perl-base: Multiple vulnerabilities - CRITICAL & HIGH
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Status: No fix available yet (fix_deferred or affected, as of 2026-06-13)
# Packages: perl-base 5.40.1-6
# Impact: Low - Perl is a base system dependency, not used directly by our app
# Note: Python application, Perl not invoked at runtime
# Mitigation: Container runs as non-root with minimal privileges
# Auto-expires: 2026-09-13 (forces re-evaluation after 3 months)

# Path traversal via crafted symlinks (CRITICAL) — shorter expiry for critical
CVE-2026-42496 exp:2026-07-13

# Heap buffer overflow when compiling (CRITICAL) — shorter expiry for critical
CVE-2026-8376 exp:2026-07-13

# Archive::Tar hardlink extraction (HIGH)
CVE-2026-42497 exp:2026-09-13

# IO::Uncompress::Unzip CPU exhaustion (HIGH)
CVE-2026-48959 exp:2026-09-13

# perl-IO-Compress arbitrary code execution (HIGH)
CVE-2026-48962 exp:2026-09-13

# Archive::Tar memory exhaustion (HIGH)
CVE-2026-9538 exp:2026-09-13

